ENTRY       EC 1.14.99.10               Enzyme
NAME        steroid 21-monooxygenase;
            steroid 21-hydroxylase;
            21-hydroxylase;
            P450c21;
            CYP21A2 (gene name)
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen;
            Miscellaneous
SYSNAME     steroid,NADPH---hemoprotein reductase:oxygen oxidoreductase (21-hydroxylating)
REACTION    a C21 steroid + [reduced NADPH---hemoprotein reductase] + O2 = a 21-hydroxy-C21-steroid + [oxidized NADPH---hemoprotein reductase] + H2O [RN:R02130]
ALL_REAC    R02130 > R02213 R02838 R03326 R03784 R03849 R04675
SUBSTRATE   C21 steroid;
            [reduced NADPH---hemoprotein reductase];
            O2 [CPD:C00007]
PRODUCT     21-hydroxy-C21-steroid;
            [oxidized NADPH---hemoprotein reductase];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
COMMENT     Requires NADPH and EC 1.6.2.4, NADPH---hemoprotein reductase. A heme-thiolate protein (P-450) enzyme responsible for the conversion of progesterone and 17alpha-hydroxyprogesterone to their respective 21-hydroxylated derivatives, 11-deoxycorticosterone and 11-deoxycortisol. Involved in the biosynthesis of the hormones aldosterone and cortisol.
HISTORY     EC 1.14.99.10 created 1961 as EC 1.99.1.11, transferred 1965 to EC 1.14.1.8, transferred 1972 to EC 1.14.99.10, modified 2013
